  "prompt": "What are common early pregnancy symptoms or signs that make you feel you may be pregnant?",
  "response": "Early pregnancy symptoms can vary from person to person, but there are several common signs that might indicate you could be pregnant. These symptoms often appear within the first few weeks after conception and may include:\n\n### 1. **Missed Period**\n   - One of the most obvious and common signs of pregnancy is a missed menstrual period. However, some women may experience light spotting or bleeding around the time of their expected period, known as implantation bleeding.\n\n### 2. **Breast Changes**\n   - Tender, swollen, or sore breasts can occur early in pregnancy due to hormonal changes. The nipples may also become more sensitive or darker in color.\n\n### 3. **Fatigue**\n   - Feeling unusually tired or exhausted is a common early sign of pregnancy, often due to increased levels of the hormone progesterone.\n\n### 4. **Nausea (Morning Sickness)**\n   - Nausea, with or without vomiting, can begin as early as two to eight weeks after conception. Despite the name, it can occur at any time of day.\n\n### 5. **Frequent Urination**\n   - Increased urination may start early in pregnancy as the growing uterus puts pressure on the bladder and hormonal changes increase blood flow to the kidneys.\n\n### 6. **Food Aversions or Cravings**\n   - Changes in taste or smell can lead to food aversions or cravings early in pregnancy. You might suddenly dislike foods you previously enjoyed or crave unusual combinations.\n\n### 7. **Mood Swings**\n   - Hormonal fluctuations can cause mood swings, irritability, or emotional sensitivity in early pregnancy.\n\n### 8. **Bloating and Cramping**\n   - Some women experience bloating, mild cramping, or a feeling similar to premenstrual symptoms early in pregnancy.\n\n### 9. **Heightened Sense of Smell**\n   - An increased sensitivity to smells is common and can contribute to nausea or food aversions.\n\n### 10. **Dizziness or Lightheadedness**\n   - Changes in blood pressure and blood sugar levels can cause dizziness or lightheadedness in early pregnancy.\n\n### 11. **Constipation**\n   - Hormonal changes can slow down the digestive system, leading to constipation.\n\n### 12. **Basal Body Temperature (BBT) Stay High**\n   - If you\u2019ve been tracking your basal body temperature, a sustained high temperature past your expected period can be an early sign of pregnancy.\n\n### When to Take a Pregnancy Test\n- If you suspect you\u2019re pregnant, take a home pregnancy test after your missed period. These tests detect the presence of the pregnancy hormone hCG (human chorionic gonadotropin). For the most accurate results, test in the morning when your urine is most concentrated.\n\nIf you experience these symptoms and get a positive pregnancy test, it\u2019s a good idea to schedule an appointment with a healthcare provider to confirm the pregnancy and begin prenatal care.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
